cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with deep learning models and their pruning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the learning dynamics of pruned models, which falls under the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper addresses questions of uniqueness and dependence on the chosen pruning method, which are relevant to the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
